pull.title: doc: Remove outdated minrelaytxfee comment
pull.body: This is no longer true after #9380

events.body:
utACK

But we should probably replace it with a more accurate comment.
I doubt any user will download and read the source code to look for documentation of command line args. The documentation should be put in the manpages.
Adding a more accurate comment could be done later - let's remove the inaccurate one at least. It's better to have no documentation comments than deceiving one.
